@startuml Identity and API Integration Patterns

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Identity & API Integration Patterns for Constrained Dual-Tenant Agents

== Pattern 1: IGA-Driven Provisioning & Entitlement (SailPoint) ==

participant "Retailer IGA /\nHR / NERM" as src
participant "SailPoint\n(Central IGA)" as sp
participant "Retail\nEntra ID (IIGRS)" as entra_r
participant "D365 F&O / CRM" as d365

src -> sp: Identity & role events\n(joiner / mover / leaver)
sp -> entra_r: SCIM provisioning\n(security groups, B2B guest,\napp roles) for non-D365 apps
sp -> d365: Direct connector\n(roles, duties, segregation\nof duties)
entra_r --> sp: Provisioning status
d365 --> sp: Assignment confirmation
note over sp
  Single source of entitlement truth
  - Non-D365 apps: Entra groups + SCIM/OIDC/SAML
  - D365 F&O/CRM: direct SailPoint connectors
  - POS users provisioned as local D365 users
end note

== Pattern 2: Coworker Access via B2B Guest (Delegated, OBO) ==

actor "Retail Coworker" as user1
participant "M365 Copilot /\nTeams (Enterprise)" as copilot1
participant "Enterprise\nEntra ID (ONEIIG)" as entra1
participant "Retail\nEntra ID (IIGRS)" as entra2
participant "Retail Agent / API" as api1

user1 -> copilot1: Invoke agent (as B2B guest)
copilot1 -> entra1: Authenticate guest principal
entra1 --> copilot1: Access token (user)
copilot1 -> entra1: OBO token exchange\n(for Retail scope)
entra1 -> entra2: Cross-tenant token\n(B2B trust, CTAS)
entra2 --> copilot1: Downstream token
copilot1 -> api1: Call with downstream token
api1 --> copilot1: Response
note over entra1, entra2
  Requires:
  - Cross-tenant access settings (CTAS)
  - B2B guest as default; member only as fallback
  - Entitlements provisioned via SailPoint (Pattern 1)
end note

== Pattern 3: Application-Only & Workload Identity Federation ==

participant "Azure Function\n(Agent Host)" as func
participant "User-Assigned\nManaged Identity" as mi
participant "Enterprise\nEntra ID (ONEIIG)" as entra5
participant "Retail\nEntra ID (IIGRS)" as entra6
participant "Retail API" as api3

func -> mi: Request token
mi -> entra5: Federated credential\n(no secrets)
entra5 --> mi: App-only token\n(consented service principal)
mi --> func: Access token
func -> api3: Call Retail API
api3 -> entra6: Validate token
entra6 --> api3: Token valid
api3 --> func: Response
note over mi
  No secrets, auto-rotation, audit trail.
  Native multi-tenant Copilot behavior is a
  FUTURE optimization, not the launch baseline.
end note

== Pattern 4: Customer Access via CIAM (Separation) ==

actor "Retail Customer" as cust
participant "CIAM\n(External ID)" as ciam
participant "Customer-facing\nApp / API" as capp

cust -> ciam: Sign-in (social / local)
ciam --> cust: CIAM token
cust -> capp: Access customer scenario
note over ciam
  Customers are NEVER provisioned as
  tenant (workforce) identities.
  CIAM is fully separate from coworker B2B paths.
end note

@enduml
